What you need to know:

While consumers are less concerned, and probably can’t tell the difference between local and imported sugar – their main concern being affordability and availability – cane growers, processors, researchers and industry analysts have asked one question; when will the sector be ready to compete?Reports indicate newer varieties with a 12-month maturity as opposed to the current 18 months, and a higher percentage of sucrose, at 15 per cent up from the usual 11 per cent have been developed.For the longest time, it has always been reported that the cartels bring in more than the allowable 200 metric tonnes.